   {:e #blake3 "5d3b31ed5216985fe2c2333cab62715b3c179e2f466f86d24beb9ae4bf59dd07" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-926421463c9ce3eb; Session entity: :recon/trace-6c2154587f60099a; Session entity: :recon/trace-27345db95d974015; Meta-Learning — Phrasing Pattern Transfer Across Projects; Session entity: :task/t-f78362d7; CE-STEER-INSIGHT: Hypothesis phrasing IS latent space navigation. The LLM already contains knowledge about Go CLIs, Cobra patterns, SQLite, event sourcing. The hypothesis STEERS the LLM to the relevant region. Different phrasings activate different latent space subspaces. 'How does A relate to B?' activates 1000 dimensions (broad). 'Does ParseDocument in document.go:L180 bypass the JSONL event stream in events/stream.go, violating APP-INV-071 log canonicality?' activates 10 dimensions (precise). The precise version converges 100x faster. Hypothesis compilation: compile_hypothesis_prompt(source_obs, target_obs, temperature, grounding) produces natural-language steering vector. High T: broad open phrasing. Medium T: grounded targeted phrasing with file paths and shared keywords. Low T: precise falsifiable phrasing with line numbers, function names, spec IDs. Phrasing calibration: hypothesis ledger tracks which phrasing patterns produce highest actual delta-F(S). System learns not just WHAT to ask but HOW to ask. Braid's entire output pipeline is a prompt compiler — every string emitted is a steering event on the LLM's latent space manifold.; Session entity: :recon/trace-bcf731a672e8ba86; CE-EXPLORE-INSIGHT: Task topology and knowledge topology are DUAL structures governed by the SAME mathematics. Both are weighted graphs with spectral decomposition, Fiedler partition, CALM classification, Cheeger quality. topology.rs already compiles task graphs into execution plans. The SAME machinery compiles knowledge graphs into exploration plans. braid explore plan --agents 3 would: (1) Build observation connection graph, (2) Spectral decomposition (eigenvalues + eigenvectors of graph Laplacian), (3) Fiedler partition into N communities, (4) CALM classify: monotonic (independent observations, parallel exploration) vs non-monotonic (contradictions, serial resolution), (5) Per-agent plans: community-specific hypotheses, bridges, seeds, estimated delta-F(S). After merge round: recompute graph, re-partition, reassign agents. Multi-agent exploration as quantum annealing: agents are parallel states exploring the energy landscape, CRDT merge is tunneling between states (escapes local minima), F(S) temperature governs exploration breadth, convergence is ground state. The spectral partition of the knowledge graph IS the optimal exploration assignment.; Session entity: :task/t-db551f02; Session entity: :task/t-877bb2c6; Session entity: :recon/trace-c31c42f721abd800; CE-COGNITION-INSIGHT: The daemon is not a cache — it is a mind. Between agent requests, the daemon should run a cognitive loop: PERCEIVE (detect filesystem/git/observation changes), CONNECT (auto-connect new observations), HYPOTHESIZE (generate temperature-adaptive bridges), SELF-INVESTIGATE (for structural hypotheses, check them autonomously — file existence, import checks, test file counts, LOC measurement — these are O(N_files) operations requiring no LLM), REFLECT (calibrate phrasing patterns from outcomes), PREPARE (cache results for instant agent response). Implementation: cognitive_tick() called every 5s in daemon main loop. investigate_structural() handles FileExists, ImportCheck, TestCoverage, LineCount. Daemon records self-investigations as observations with agent=braid:daemon. When agent connects, status shows 'Since your last session, I investigated 5 structural hypotheses. Found: parser has 0 test files, document.go does NOT import events package. Your investigation: does this bypass violate APP-INV-071?' The daemon does the structural homework so the LLM agent can focus on semantic reasoning. This IS active inference: perception + thinking + action + reflection. ~200 LOC in daemon.rs.; Session entity: :task/t-c1999149; Daemon Cognitive Loop — Active Inference; CE-META-INSIGHT: Three levels of learning. Level 1 Object: learn about the Go CLI (observations). Level 2 Meta: learn which questions produce best answers (hypothesis ledger — predicted vs actual delta-F(S) per hypothesis TYPE). Level 3 Meta-Meta: learn which QUESTIONING STRATEGIES transfer across projects. Implementation: when hypothesis H with phrasing pattern P produces delta-F(S) outcome O, record (P, O) in :meta/phrasing-pattern datoms. Patterns: file-path-grounded, falsification-framed, observation-text-reusing, cross-package-bridging, void-exploring. Over sessions, compute per-pattern accuracy. When braid is deployed on NEW project, import Level 2+3 patterns via CRDT merge of calibration datoms. Compound interest: each project makes braid better at ALL future projects. Not because domain facts transfer (they dont) but because questioning strategies transfer (C8 substrate-independent). After 10 projects, first hypothesis on project 11 is as good as 50th hypothesis on project 1. ~100 LOC in routing.rs for pattern tracking + merge.; CE-TOPO-INSIGHT: The knowledge graph is a simplicial complex. H0 = connected components (knowledge islands — what FEGH detects). H1 = loops (circular reasoning — A explains B explains C explains A with no external grounding). H2 = voids (bounded unknown territory — boundary mapped but interior unexplored, HIGHEST VALUE targets). Currently FEGH only targets H0 holes. H1 detection would identify circular reasoning defects requiring FALSIFICATION hypotheses. H2 detection would identify bounded unknowns requiring EXPLORATION hypotheses. Three Socratic strategies from hole type: H0 bridge 'How does X relate to Y?', H1 falsification 'X explains Y explains X — what EXTERNAL evidence confirms this?', H2 void 'You mapped the boundary of Z but not inside — what is in there?'. Betti numbers beta0 beta1 beta2 are computable from the knowledge complex. Euler characteristic chi=beta0-beta1+beta2 is a single convergence metric. As learning proceeds: beta0 decreases (bridges connect), beta1 increases then decreases (loops form then break), beta2 increases then decreases (voids detected then explored). Implementation: compute_betti_numbers(connection_graph) using existing spectral machinery. Surface in braid status as 'topology: N components, M loops, K voids'. ~100 LOC.\nSession entity: :task/t-5db2efb0; Hypothesis Prompt Compilation; Session entity: :task/t-e7394fd8; Session entity: :task/t-d7dd2d4c; Topological Hole Detection — Betti Numbers; Session entity: :task/t-46dff538" :op :assert}
